headlines.description: — Devonte Graham had 24 points and nine assists, P.J. Washington chipped in with 22 points and 12 rebounds and the Charlotte Hornets defeated the Boston Celtics 125-104 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Graham scores 24 as Hornets rout Celtics 125-104

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 33 points in his latest return from injury, Kyrie Irving had 34 and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Phoenix Suns 128-119 on Sunday in a matchup of two of the NBA's top teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 33 points in return, Nets beat Suns 128-119

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 28 points and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Portland Trail Blazers for the second time in three days, 120-113 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has 28 points, Grizzlies beat Blazers again, 120-113

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 33 points and the Washington Wizards rallied to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 119-110 on Sunday night for their eighth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards rally to beat Cavaliers for 8th straight victory

headlines.description: — Lou Williams sank four 3-pointers in the final seven minutes, including a jumper that gave Atlanta its first lead of the second half, Bogdan Bogdanovic scored 32 points and the Hawks beat the Milwaukee Bucks 111-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lou Williams' hot shooting helps Hawks beat Bucks 111-104

headlines.description: — Malcolm Brogdon scored 24 points and the Indiana Pacers used a big third quarter to rout short-handed Orlando 131-112 on Sunday night in a game marred by Magic rookie Devin Cannady’s gruesome ankle injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic rookie Cannady' breaks ankle in loss to Pacers

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 37 points and set an NBA record for 3-pointers in a month at 85, leading the Golden State Warriors past the Sacramento Kings 117-113 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry sets NBA record for 3-pointers in a month with 85
